                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d739">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.733/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Trueblood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-15T11:00:00-04:32"
                            >April 15, 1931—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. Manager of the All America Cables notified the Legation yesterday that
                    beginning today he would be required by the Government to collect the taxes
                    prescribed by the law of February 14th, 1929, on all cables except press and
                    Bolivian official. Tax on Legation’s cables to the Department will amount to 20
                    centavos per word plus 50 centavos message. Will protest to Foreign Office on
                    grounds international comity subject to the Department’s approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Trueblood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
